Choices:  A: car B: fuel system C: accelerate D: boat E: airplane<n>Output:		E<n><n>## 题 题 描述:给定两个列表 A 和 B，对于每个相同元素， A 中的元素都大于 B。如果 A 中某个元素为 B，，请将此元素移除并返回第一个不以此元素开头的子序列 A1.<n><n>输入: A = [10,8,6,0,100,55], B= [0,1]<n>输出:  [10,8]<n>  <n>输入:<n>A = [10,1,0,7]，　B = [1,0,3]<n>Output: [1, 0, 7]<n>  <n>输出: [10,8]->1,8<n><n>## 思路:<n>给定一个 A 和 B，首先让 A 递归删除掉全部的 B 中的元素，在 B 去掉 A 中的元件同时在 A 中找 的时候再执行 A 去 B 中的元件，重复删除 B，直到己遍历整个 A。<n><n>## 程序:<n>```go<n>package main<n>//删除排序数组中大于某个指定值的所有元素的子序列,输入:当元成都序列大于某一值时， 在数组中删除所有大了这一值的的元素（跳过此过程做后遍厝<n>func delete(list []int, start int) []int {<n>	if list[start] > list[start+1] {<n>		for x := start + 1; x < len(list); x++ {<n>			m := list[x]<n>			j := x + 1<n>			for j < len(list) {<n>				m = list[j]<n>				if j+1 < len(list) && m > list[j+1] {<n>

He continues till he puts the last peg on the bottom right corner of the board and captures that corner. There is no peg from the game in the start. The captured pegs become permanent and remain with the player. To make the game exciting, the other player is given the choice to start the game with 2 pegs only and captures the first right corner from the start. The second player now tries to capture the corner first and go on till the last corner. He has an advantage because, from start there are two pegs to defend. But, he can not decide what choice to make. What should he choose so that the other player does not get to occupy more space around the first right corner?<n>Output: e<n>			<n>Input: A shop is selling a radio. The radio is priced 1999. The shop offers a discount of 21 per cent on it

A box has two identical identical balls. these balls weigh 50 g each and weighs 100 grams when empty. the box is kept in a room of 20 degree celsius. what is the value of θ?<n><n><n>Output:<n><n>37.8<n><n><n>Solution:<n><n><n><n>If a box contains a ball of 50 g, with the box and two balls it weighs 110 g (2 balls each with 50 g + box with 10 g). with 2 balls each and box the weight of it is 110 g and with one ball and box it is 100 g. so when one ball is subtracted the box weighs 1 gram.<n><n><n>So when 1 ball is subtracted to make it one ball, the box weighs,10 g and then subtracting the ball the box weighs. (110 - 10 - 15) g.<n><n>So it weighs 95 g.<n><n><n>So 95 - (95/110)g =. g<n><n><n>Or 95 - g/(110/95) = g<n><n><n>Substitution<n><n>95(110/0.95) =. g<n><n>95(95/0.95 =. g<n><n>.<n><n><n>95/0.094 =. g<n><n>1035=.g<n><n> 100 =. g<n><n>47 grams =. g<n><n>Solution:37.8<n>

So its even number will be divisable by 5 too.<n><n>if it contains no number divisable by 3 and 5. then the whole sequence should be divisable by 15 too.<n><n>#### If I am getting 3 odd numbers from the question then I should check the sequence of number for its divisibility by 9 since:<n><n>For division by 9, If the sequence starts (4,6,8,10,12,14,16,...), ends (2,4,6...)<n><n>the sequence is (8,7,6...)<n><n>It contains no 7 and 9,so the sequence is divisable by 7<n><n>Again the sequence contains no 8 and 9 and ends with 8. So it contains only one 7 and 8. so the sequence is not divisable by 7.<n><n>

We need to determine which element in the list is closer to the two parameters. It might seem like this should be a simple matter of comparing the two parameters to all elements and finding the smallest. But Python’s list is ordered and if we have two parameters, only one can truly be closer to either parameter. Which one is the matter of sorting the list. The element 10 will clearly be closer to parameter -1. But how do we determine this?<n><n>Input: -1 100<n>

Choices:  A: bowl of soup B: serving dish C: table setting D: placemat E: glass of iced tea<n>Output:		C<n><n><n>## 문제이름: Pair Programming 및 메모리 이슈 모국어 테스트 챈지<n>### Instruction:<n><n>1) Pair Programming<n><n> 응수자가 선생님과 함께 10개의 문제이며 `워킹코드`가 지정되어있다.<n><n> 읽었다 한 문제 500ms - 600ms 내에 풀면 입양 혹은 캐릭터 2개로 고정하기<n><n> 입증액체에서 `각각 공간매점`을 바꿔서 대회를 진행하면 된다.<n><n>2) <n> 문제 16<n><n><n>      input:Find the volume of the box having the dimensions ( x =1.5, y =1.166, z = 2.8 )<n>      워킍코드 - `box * -4.48`<n><n> 챈지-  box = 10 + 10 + 0.5 * ( y * ( 1 + 1 ) + x * ( 1 - 1 ) ) * z <n>                   = 10 +10 + 0  * (  ( ( 1 + 0 ) - 1 ) * 2.8) <n>                   =10 +10 - 0.8<n>                                  =10<n><n><n>          output:80<n>		<n><n><n>### Instruction<n><n>1) Input:<n><n>			find the greatest common divisor of 1804, 60, 70<n><n>			a -> 1 & 2 & 3 & 4<n><n>			1) input 1804 60 70 <n><n>

Each time the for loop is evaluated, it returns an output and the original expression is reevaluated.<n><n>### Instruction<n>If a for loop is evaluated n times, the output will consist of a line each time the loop condition is true, and one for the final time when the loop condition is false.<n>Output to the loop’s standard output is written in line with the return value of the expression evaluated at the current iteration of the loop, with each iteration being separated by a newline (called a newline character) at the end of the line. For loops are very flexible and powerful, but are also very dangerous and difficult to debug.<n><n>#### Input:<n><n>What is the output of the program?<n><n>Programmer_1:<n>```<n>for(i=0; i<10; i++){<n>    for(j=0; j<3; j++)<n>        printf("%i \n",i*i);<n>}<n>```<n><n>Programs_2:<n>```<n>i=j=3;<n>

Choices:  A: asia B: southern hemisphere C: planet D: east E: earth<n>Output:		C/D<n><n># <n>## Solution<n><n>### Solution:<n>-140 is given<n>-Mean: = 30\*140<n>-Therefore X = 42<n>-New Mean: = 30*42<n>-Hence,correct Mean: = 140.2<n><n>### Solution 2:<n>-Ans: Answer: (D) 1378.5<n><n>-Total Volume:  L  * D^3<n>-where D = 34 + 8 + 35 = 83<n>Given:  L = 25 + 24 + 19 + 18 = 78<n><n><n>-Hence,Volume=25 + 23.125 + 19.375 + 17.625 = 80.7<n>-Therefore, % of error:  error = (80.7 - 78) / 80.7*100 = 3.5%<n><n>### Solution<n>-Cash Value : Rs. 500<n>-Sale value : Rs.637.5<n>-profit = 637.5 – 500 = Rs.137.5<n>Average of 6 numbers : ((a + b) + (2\*\*b + 3) + (4\*\*B + 5) + (6\*\*B)) / 6<n><n>### Solution :<n><n>-1\*5/6 = 25/ = 37.5 (answer is 37.5)<n>-2\*5/6 * 37.5 = answer<n><n>### Solution(3)<n><n>-Hence, 30\*42 = 664<n>-Hence, correct mean: 140.6 and 140.4 if 2 decimal places are required. Choices:  A: new york B: whorehouse C: street corner D: corner of two streets E: brother<n>Output:		whorehouse/street corner<n><n>## Solution:<n><n>This question is tricky because the average is defined as the sum of all values in the sample divided by the number of values in the sample. The average is always the same, so if one value in the sample is swapped it does not change the average value.<n><n>However it does change the arithmetic mean which is the sum of all of the values divided by the total number of values which was not stated.<n>

Choices:  A: jewelery B: fort knox C: church D: jewelry store E: treasure chest<n>Output:		A<n><n><!-- ASSIGNED TO: Aman.Chhabra, Manmeetkaur, PratyakshSinghSingh, Gurpreetkaur, Jaskiratkaur, Jagdeepkaur --><n><!-- BATCH: 2.1.9 --><n><n>##### Solution:<n>```java<n><n>import java.util.*;<n><n>public class Hackerrank {<n>	@SuppressWarnings("unused")<n>	public static void main(String[] args) {<n>		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);<n>		int t = sc.nextInt();<n>		while (t-- > 0) {<n>			int a = sc.nextInt(), b = sc.nextInt()-1, c = sc.nextInt().intValue();<n>			Hackerrank.solve(a, b, c);<n>		}<n>		sc.close();<n>	}<n><n>	private static void solve(int a, int b, int c) {<n>		boolean ans = false;//initializing  variables <n>		int total=0;<n>		if(a<=b||b<=0)<n>		{<n>			return;<n>		}<n><n>		for(int i=1;i<=b;i++)<n>		{<n><n>			if(((b/a)*total+1)==c)//initializing  variables  <n>			{<n>	   			ans=true;<n>				return; <n>			}<n>	   	 if(total==c || (b/a)==c)<n>			{	<n>				ans=false;<n>			}	<n>		   total+=i;<n>		} <n><n>	   	if( ans == true) <n>		{<n>            System.out.println("YES");<n>            return;<n>		}   <n>	   <n>	   System.out.println( "NO" );<n>		<n>	}<n>}<n>```

Input the correct numerical value on lines A-G<n><n>C. Calculate the following<n><n>Output:<n><n>Answer each of the following questions by giving a reason / solution.<n><n>-The data set contains 35 numbers between 1 and 99, how many values will be missed?<n><n>Let the data set be X.<n>Now there are (35-1) possibilities to fill these missing values. That's because there are x-1 elements, each with x-1 ways to be filled in. We have (35-1)*1 = 34 numbers, and not enough missing values.<n><n>-The maximum of 35 numbers is 96. How many of them are greater than 96?<n><n>Let the maximum value be x<n>We don't need the largest possible value that can fit in range<n>35 numbers between 2 and 96. We can fill in the remaining values, and that's why we know that 34 numbers equal to 96.<n><n>-Three squares of 2 by 2 matrices fill the whole board. How many white squares does the third matrix need?<n><n>Let the three matrices be l, m and n<n>Let the number of white squares be y, and the number of black squares be y-1<n>3-squared matrixes fill the complete board (each has one white square, two black squares).<n>So we can fill the two remaining black squares, and that's how y=2.<n><n>The sum of the squares of two numbers between 1 and $35$ is 15 what are the numbers?<n>Let the sum of the square be s,<n>We know the sum of the squares of the first 2 numbers is 1.<n>If we assume the sum of the squares is s,<n>Then the 2 numbers can be,<n>2^2 + a^2, for a in (1, 35)<n>15 = 1 + (2^2 + a2), for every a in (1,35)<n>2^2 + 3^2 + 4^2 + 5^2 + 6^2 + 7^2 + 8^2 + 9^2<n>14 = 1 +

Choices:  A: rural area B: africa C: ohio D: big city E: tribe<n>Output:		C<n><n>Input: 10, 20, 30, 40, 14?<n>Output:10<n>```<n><n>## <a name="run-the-program"></a>Corrigere le questioni<n>Per modificare questo codice in C, creare un nuovo progetto della riga A o C con una semplice definizione di classi:<n><n>```c<n>#include <iostream><n>using namespace std;<n><n>class Solution<n>{<n>    public:<n>    float solve(int n)  //function to store the input and to find and display the output<n>    {<n>        float total = 0;<n>        int num;<n><n>        do <n>        {<n>            //take input of numbers (n-1) times<n>             cin>> num;<n>        } <n>        while ( num <= n ); <n><n>        while ( num > 0 ) <n>        {<n>             total += num % 10;  //add input of remaining numbers to total<n>             num /= 10; <n>        } <n><n>        return total;<n>    }<n><n>    void displayResult()   //function to display the result<n>    {<n>        cout<< ""<<endl;<n><n>        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) <n>        {<n>                   if (i % n == 0)<n>                   {<n>                   //print if n is div by i<n>                   cout << " n / " << i << =  endl<n>                   << solution(i) << endl;// print the result of  n / i<n>                   }<n>        }<n><n>    }<n><n>}; //end of class<n><n>int main ()<n>{<n>Solution obj = Solution();<n>obj.displayResult();<n>return 0;<n>} //end of main <n>```<n><n>Questo codice creerà un'app di.Net denominata `Solution`. Per usarlo, importare il file.NET con il nome seguente: `Solution.sln`. <n><n>```<n>    #r "Solution.dll"<n>```<n><n>Press `F5` to build la soluzione ed eseguire il codice. La soluzione restituisce un array, che può essere visualizzato usando [Visual Studio di nuovo](visualstudio.md).

(NOT MOD / AND / OR / XOR) You can multiply, shift right, shift left, and xor. There can be any number of operands for shift operations, in that case you can make them all the same size, and shift right any number of times. Do not use division, modulo, power, or any standard bit operations. You are allowed to do as many calculations as you need, for example. you can divide into 1 million steps

At T : Finish Time + distance.<n>Therefore,<n>(M - T) * (M - T) = N * N<n>M * M + M * N - N * N = M * M - N * N<n>M + 3.5 * M - M * N = M * (M - N)<n>2 * M - 3.5 * N = (M - N)M<n>2 * N - 3.5 = (M - N),<n>2 * N = N- 3.5<n>The sum of a number and a number 3.5 times its product equals 3.5 times the number <n>Output: T<n><n>Input: The following are terms of a certain arithmetic sequence except that the next term is 19.<n>The common difference between the terms of this sequence is<n> 1 ) 4<n> 2 ) 5<n> 3 ) 14<n> 4 ) 11<n> 5 ) 17<n>Output: 3) 14<n><n>Input : A rectangular garden is 8 by 16 yards in dimensions. Solution: 987654321<n><n>#!/usr/bin/python<n><n>from sys import stdin<n><n>if __name__ == "__main__":<n>    fd = stdin.read()<n>    if fd:<n>        pass<n>\end{code}<n><n>Now when i am executing this program it's throwing an error like:<n><n>\begin{blockquote}<n><n>ValueError: need precision<n>\end{blockquote}<n><n>Can anyone help me out with this issue.<n><n>Comment: This has nothing to do with the original question you asked, but this is what the error message means: http://stackoverflow.com/a/7073606/1205170.<n><n>Comment: yes right but i need solution because this question is part of my programming assignment<n><n>Answer: Python uses the `decimal` module for floating point calculations. If the data isn't exactly correct, then it will have to introduce round-off error. Since the round-off error is unknown, it can't be used so it reports this error.<n><n>There are several different solutions to this problem, but the most basic is just to convert to a float.<n><n>\begin{code}<n>if 1:<n>    a = float("{}".format(something))<n>\end{code}, where `something` is `int` that you can multiply by a "large" number to get to your `float`. If you are already using `float` instead of a `decimal` already, you don't need to do this.<n><n>Comment: I can't believe this was answered almost 2 years ago!  But this answer helped me a lot today!  Thanks!

This is mean<n><n>Input: Volume of the largest sphere that we can inscribe in the box is (1) π * (24cm) *(18cm) = 961π cm3,<n>(2) π * (144cm) *(24cm) =11728π cm3<n>(3)  π * (135cm) * (24cm)=  9975π cm3<n>(4)  π * (96cm) * (23cm) = 7052π cm3<n>(5) (3). Choices:  A: jewelry store B: case C: hock D: watch store E: pawn<n>Output:		D<n><n>### Instruction:Answer the questions below in a word or a sentence.<n><n>Question 1. a cube of 8 units side measurable 56, in which every edge is cut down by 1 / 7 unit. what is the volume of the 3d solid after cutting?<n><n>Explanation :<n><n>The volume of 3d solid after cube cut down is the volume of the remaining 3d solid ( that is after cube cut down ).<n><n>The cube cut down is a 3d solid of :<n><img src="/public_html/study/files/uploads/QR0001.png" width="80%"><n>The required 3d solid is the 3d solid of:<n><img src="/Public_html/study-images/QR00301.png" /><n><n>The volume of the cutting cube is 16, and the volume of the cube after cutting is 4, the volume of the cutting cube after cutting is 1 / 7 of the cutting cube before cutting.<n><n>The volume of cutting cube before cutting ( and after cutting ) is 64, the 3d volume of cutting cube is 128 which is the cube of 64, then the volume of the cube before cutting is 64.<n><n>Then the 3d volume before cutting is the volume of the original 3d cube ( which is 160 ).<n><n>From the above : the volume of 3d cut down cube is 32.<n><n>The volume of remaining 3d solid after the cutting of cutting cube is the volume of original 3d cube - 32 = 128 - 32 =126.<n><n>Option Choice : C<n><n>### Instructions:The following statements contain terms/phrases in italics which are underlined.
